race.comment: GO GETABOY (1) grows a leg over this course and distance with four wins and three placings from just seven attempts and has saluted on all going. Sure to be right there when the judge calls a halt. VALENKI (2) was a touch disappointing at the latest outing but the form prior was full of merit. Can bounce right back without surprising. FODOR (3) has only missed a drum once in six starts over this track and trip and maps ideally from the inside alley. In the mix. SPIRIT MEISTER (6) is a six-time winner here who shouldn't be slept on. Worth including in all wider plays. CRYSTAL CHIEF (5) is also in contention after a sound second over 1200m at Atherton, only beaten 0.9 lengths.
